            "currentCldrName": "Person Tipping Hand",
            "description": "<p>A person tipping their hand by their shoulder as if they&rsquo;re carrying a tray of drinks or flipping their hair. Originally called <em>Information Desk Person</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This emoji is commonly used to express sassiness or sarcasm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While no gender is specified, <a href=\"/apple/ios-4.0/person-tipping-hand/\">many</a> <a href=\"/twitter/twemoji-1.0/person-tipping-hand/\">early</a> <a href=\"/google/android-4.4/person-tipping-hand/\">designs</a>&nbsp;displayed this emoji as a woman. Google&rsquo;s 2014 design shows <a href=\"/google/android-5.0/person-tipping-hand/\">a blob wearing white gloves and a pillbox hat</a>. Microsoft&rsquo;s 2015 design shows <a href=\"/microsoft/windows-10/person-tipping-hand/\">a woman doing this gesture while winking</a>, a facial expression that further reinforces the sassy and sarcastic uses of this emoji.</p>",
